Class Module

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.uu.cs.ape.sat.models.logic.constructs.TaxonomyPredicate
      • nl.uu.cs.ape.sat.models.AbstractModule
        • nl.uu.cs.ape.sat.models.Module
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Predicate

    public class Module
extends AbstractModule
    The Module class represents concrete modules/tools that can be used in our program. It must be annotated using the proper Input/Output pair provided by the tool annotation file.
    Author:
    Vedran Kasalica

      • generateModule

        public static Module generateModule(java.lang.String moduleName,
                                    java.lang.String moduleID,
                                    java.lang.String rootNode,
                                    AllModules allModules,
                                    AbstractModule superModule,
                                    Module_Execution moduleExecution)
        The class is used to check weather the Module with @moduleID was already introduced earlier on in @allModules. In case it was defined as it returns the item, in case of it being introduced as an AbstractModule, it is extended to a Module and returned, otherwise the new element is generated and returned.

        In case of generating a new Module, the object is added to the set of all the Modules and added as a subModule to the parent Module.
        Parameters:
        moduleName - - Module name.
        moduleID - - Unique module identifier.
        rootNode - - ID of the Taxonomy Root node corresponding to the Module.
        allModules - - Set of all the modules created so far.
        Returns:
        The Module representing the item.
